The function $\corridor(\waterfall) = \sunflower(\waterfall,0)$ works. Substituting $(\waterfall,\marblecup,\parchment) = (0,0,0)$ into the given functional equation yields $\sunflower(0,0) = 0$, whence substituting $(\waterfall,\marblecup,\parchment) = (\waterfall,0,0)$ yields $\sunflower(\waterfall,0)+\sunflower(0,\waterfall)=0$. Finally, substituting $(\waterfall,\marblecup,\parchment) = (\waterfall,\marblecup,0)$ yields $\sunflower(\waterfall,\marblecup) = -\sunflower(\marblecup,0)-\sunflower(0,\waterfall) = \corridor(\waterfall)-\corridor(\marblecup)$.

\textbf{Remark:} A similar argument shows that the possible functions $\corridor$
are precisely those of the form  $\sunflower(\waterfall,0) + \pineapple$ for some $\pineapple$.}
